However, if a line isn't visible on the screen, it won't be cleared, so positioning yourself so that you can't see certain blocks when you go to clear lines really helps.

Level 004: Self-Testing

If you do collect a burning wood block, the unburned version gets added to your inventory, so don't worry about being singed. Also, doing this can stop a chain of wood blocks from all burning up, but don't break a burning chain at a bad time, or you might make a puzzle unsolvable.
Now this part takes a good deal of thought. You don't want to just clear lines blindly, or you'll destroy the ore that you need for the upgrade.

A bit of cleverness can save you blocks here. If a block of gravel lands on another block, it stops falling, and won't fall again if that block underneath it is removed and the gravel is walked on again.
If you're carrying enough blocks with you when you clear a level, you'll earn a star. In most levels, the requirement is the absolute maximum number of blocks you could have.
Ehh, if I was fast, I could've saved a couple of wood blocks over there, but they're not important.
Each level of the main story has a treasure chest in it somewhere, but I'm intentionally going to avoid picking any of them up in this run (even if they're directly in my path).

The chest in this level is to the right, but you'd have to carefully jump over all of the fire slimes to reach it, and then survive the way back and then complete the level to keep it.
